column5: Went down to the Lower River today.......visability was less than a foot.  Got one rainbow on a kwickfish and two browns on shinners.  It was about a 40 minute bite.

Good fishin.  How do you like those lake o. browns?  I used to catch them by the fistful in the winter but never kept since everyone I talked to said the meat looked and felt more like mashed potatoes than flesh.
Attaboy Corvy  Great job  Some good eats for the smoker
Corvy...you da man!  Great catches.  I want to steal your boat too
Good bag o' fish! Sounds like it was a tough day, but you guys still did well. Kudos
Nice days work there.  Could be searching for some of those tomorow myself.
thanks for all the replys guys. fished today in a tourny on the lower vis was less then 6 inch's today we cought a skunk as did many
Nice  Now Im tempted to take my boat out  Thanks for sharing C
Doug... your not the only one with white stripes
i hear you leech we all get them boy does it suck
No kidding Doug    but redemption is a b_itch... going back soon
Nice fish.......all I keep hearing is the river will NOT clear up this year.....no ice on Erie and lots of wind and some rain is not a good recipe for the lower river.
